This .gitignore file covers:
- Visual Studio-specific files and folders
- Build artifacts and debug/release directories
- User-specific settings
- Test results
- .idea folder for JetBrains IDEs (Rider, IntelliJ)
- Additional system-specific files like .DS_Store
- Visual Studio Code settings
- Rider-specific files

You can save this as `.gitignore` in the root of your project. It will help keep your repository clean by excluding unnecessary files from version control.